A Hong Kong-registered oil tanker leaked 10,810 tonsor 66,000 barrelsof crude oil off South Korea's stormy west coast on Fridayin what was estimated to be the nation's largest maritime oil spill.
About 10.5 million liters of crude oil leaked to waters off the western coast of South Korea on Friday after an oil tanker and a barge collided early on the day and became the largest offshore oil spill in South Korea.
The previously largest oil spill in South Korea happened in 1995 when about 5,035 tonsof crude and fuel oil was leakedaccording to South Korea's Yonhap news agency.
